  "prompt": "What are some of the best interview question ever asked?",
  "response": "Here are some legendary and thought-provoking interview questions from top companies:\n\n1. Google\n- \"How many golf balls can fit in a school bus?\"\n- \"If you were to redesign a Google product, which would it be and why?\"\n\n2. Apple\n- \"Tell me about a time you faced a challenging problem and how you solved it.\"\n- \"What's the most significant thing you've learned in your career?\"\n\n3. Amazon\n- \"Tell me about a time when you had to work with a difficult team member.\"\n- \"What would you do if you saw someone doing something unethical?\"\n\n4. Microsoft\n- \"If you were a tree, what type of tree would you be and why?\"\n- \"Describe a complex technical problem you've solved.\"\n\n5. Facebook/Meta\n- \"What would you do if you had unlimited resources?\"\n- \"How would you explain a complex technical concept to a non-technical person?\"\n\n6. Interesting Behavioral Questions\n- \"Tell me about a time you failed and what you learned from it.\"\n- \"Describe a situation where you had to lead without formal authority.\"\n\n7. Creative Problem-Solving Questions\n- \"How would you move Mount Fuji?\"\n- \"Design an alarm clock for a deaf person.\"\n\nThese questions test critical thinking, problem-solving skills, creativity, and personality beyond just technical abilities.",
